>Jātarūpa
yasyeti | yasyākhilavastuviṣayeṇa mahatā jñānena dayayā ca sindhoḥ samudrasya | agādhasyānyair anadhigatajñānadayāpāratvād gambhīrasya | guṇā maitrīkṣamopaśamādayaḥ | anaghāḥ kāmakrodhaprabhavadoṣarahitāḥ | so 'kṣayo nityaparipūrṇatvād anapacayo dayāsindhutvāt paramakāruṇiko bhogalālasena śrīye sampattaye ca punaḥ samsārakleśabhayād amṛtāya mokṣāya ca | jñānasindhutvād vimalabuddhir bodharūpo bhagavān bho dhīrāḥ sevyatām | yasya sindhor agādhasya guṇāḥ śrījanmabhūmitvapīyūṣaprabhavatvādayaḥ | anaghā avināśinaḥ | so 'kṣayo nityaparipūrṇatvān mahājalanidhiḥ | śriye cāmṛtāya pīyūṣāya ca | tadarthināṃ sevituṃ yogya eva | nānucitavidhānam etat | atra jñānadayābhyāṃ sindhur iti vigṛhya tṛtīyā iti yogavibhāgāt samāsaḥ | tṛtīyā ca tṛtīyāvidhāne prakṛtyādibhya upasaṅkhyānam ity aupasaṅkhyānikī | sindhuśabdaś ca sindhur iva pūrṇaḥ | sindhur iti gauṇo 'yam | athavā sarve śabdā guṇasamudāye vartante kvacid ekadeśe 'pi iti paripūrṇatāṃ guṇam abhidhāya tad eva ca nimittam upādāya sindhuśabdo 'yaṃ tadvati devatāviśeṣe vartate | jñānadayākṛtā ca sā tasya paripūrṇateti tṛtīyā tat kṛtārthena... iti samāsaḥ | tṛtīyā ca kartṛkaraṇayoḥ... ity anenaiva || ॰ ||
>Kavikāmadhenu
[ayaṃ heturūpako 'laṃkāraḥ | tad yathā ‘gāmbhīryeṇa] samudro 'si’ iti | tasyāgādhatvaṃ yathoktaguṇavattayātulatvam | ‘duḥkhainovyasaneṣv agham’ ity abhidhānād anaghaguṇatvaṃ sukhahetulaghutvavispaṣṭatvādi | sevā śrutacintāvyākhyānādiḥ | akṣayatvaṃ saṃpūrṇatā | sarvanāmaśabdaiḥ prakrāntasya liṅgam ādīyate prakāśyamānasya vā | tad yathā ‘karmaṇā yam abhipraiti sa saṃpradānam’, ‘aṇau yat_ karma ṇau cet_ sa kartā’ | tad atra kāmacārāc chrutatvāc ca prakrāntasyaiva sindhuśabdasya liṅgena sa iti nirdeśo na nāmaliṅgānuśāsanaśabdasya | śrīs trivargasaṃpattiḥ | tad uktaṃ vyāḍinā lakṣmīsarasvatīdhītrivargasampad_vibhūtiśobhāsu | upakaraṇaveśaracanāvidhāsu ca śrīr iti prathitā || iti | athavā yā vāṅ_mayasarvajñatvalakṣaṇā svārthasaṃpat, yā ca taddhetukā trivargahetuḥ parārthasaṃpat_ tadubhayī śrīḥ | svaparārthasaṃpadā ca puṇyajñānasaṃbhārād_ yatnāt_ prāpto mokṣo 'mṛtam iti |
>Nāmacandrikā
iha khalu śrīmān amarasiṃhaś cikīrṣitasya nāmaliṅgānuśāsananāmakakoṣasya niṣpratyūhaparisamāptikāmanayā kṛtaṃ maṅgalaṃ śiṣyaśikṣāyai granthaprārambhe nibadhnāti — yasyeti || ‘bho antevāsinaḥ ! yuṣmābhiḥ’ ity adhyāhāryam | agādhasyāpārasya jñānadayāsiṃdhor mokṣadhīkṛpāsāgarasya yasya anaghā nirdoṣā guṇāḥ kṣamādayaḥ santi so 'kṣayo avināśī dhīrā jñānaprado vibhuḥ parameśvaraḥ śriye saṃpattaye amṛtāya muktaye ca sevyatām || 1 ||
>Padacandrikā
abhīṣṭadevatānamaskārādyupanītam adṛṣṭaṃ hi vighnāparanāmakasādhyapratibandhakādharmatirodhānadvārā prāripsitaṃ parisamāpayatīti prāmāṇikam ato niṣpratyūhaprāripsitaparisamāptihetusveṣṭadevatāsaṃkīrtanād_ viśiṣṭādṛṣṭam ut_pipādayiṣur granthakāraḥ prathamapadyaṃ nibabandha — yasyeti | he ’dhīrāḥ’ ! ’sa’ bhagavān ’sevyatām’ ārādhyatām | dhairyaśālina eva sevituṃ śaknuvantīti tān_ eva saṃbodhayati prakṛtatvāt | ‘yuṣmābhi’r hitecchubhiḥ | sa kaḥ ? ‘yasya guṇā’ maitrīkṣamādayo 'ṇimādayo vā | ‘anaghā’ niṣpāpā rāgādyasaṃvalitā iti yāvat | yad vā — ‘anaghā’ hṛdyāḥ | tathā ca dharaṇiḥ — anagho 'pāpahṛdyayor iti | guṇyante abhyasyante iti guṇāḥ | guṇa āmantraṇe | karmaṇi ghañ | yasya kiṃbhūtasya ? ‘jñānadayāsindhoḥ’ | ‘jñānaṃ’ samastaviṣayāvabodhaḥ | dṛṣṭaṃ svārtham anapekṣya paraduḥkhaprahāṇecchā ‘dayā’ | tayor ambutulyayoḥ sindhur iva sindhur itirūpakam | tābhyāṃ sindhur iva sindhur iti vā | prakṛtyāditvād_ vā tṛtīyā | “tṛtīye”ti yogavibhāgāt_ samāsa iti sarvadharādayaḥ | sindhuśabdo 'tra vipulādhāratvād upacaritaḥ | sindhusāmyam_ āha — ‘agādhasya’ anavacchinnamahimno anyair anavagatajñānapāratvād aparicchedyagāmbhīryasya vā | sa kiṃbhūtaḥ ? ‘akṣayaḥ’ parahitāpādāneṣu nāsti kṣayo virāmo yasya iti akṣayaḥ, maraṇarāhityād_ vā | phalaṃ vinā kathaṃ prekṣāvat-pravṛttir ata āha — ‘śriye ca’ ity ādi | śrīr atra trivargasampattiḥ | tāṃ prāptum | “kriyārthopapadasya ca” ity ādinā caturthī | tathā ca vyāḍiḥ — “lakṣmīsarasvatītrivargasampattibhūtiśobhāsūpakaraṇaveśaracanāvidhāsu ca śrir iti prathitā ||” iti | ‘amṛtāya’ ca mokṣāya ca | cakāradvayam ubhayaprādhānyadyotanārtham | bhogecchubhiḥ śriye, mumukṣubhir mokṣāya ity arthaḥ | etena hitāhitajño hitaiṣī īśitā ca, ataḥ sevārha — iti viśeṣaṇānām abhiprāyaḥ | samudrapakṣe — ‘sa sindhuḥ‘ samudraḥ sevyatām | sa kaḥ ? ‘yasya’ agādhasya atalasparśasya, ‘akṣayasya’ sadā paripūrṇasya, ‘asya’ viṣṇoḥ ‘kṣayasya’ nivāsasya vā | ‘guṇā’ nairmalyādayaḥ | ‘anaghā’ hṛdyāḥ, ratnākaratvād atiśayasphuṭībhūtāḥ | ‘jñānaṃ’ jñaptiḥ | ‘dā’ dānam | tayo ‘īḥ’ lakṣmīḥ | ‘jñānade’ gaṅgā | tayā upalakṣitasya | ‘śrīye’ lakṣmyai, ‘amṛtāya’ pīyūṣāya ca | sindhur api surāsurair lakṣmyai sudhāyai ca sevitaḥ | sevatir atra pakṣe anuśīlanārthaḥ | yathā — “striyaṃ sevata” iti | atrā'nukto 'pi vākye lakṣaṇārtho jñānadayādibhiḥ sphuṭaṃ pratīyate | na ca neyatādoṣaḥ, pratyuta prasādo nāma arthaguṇa evāyam | tad uktaṃ sarasvatīkaṇṭhābharaṇe — “yat tu prākaṭyam arthasya prasādaḥ so 'bhidhīyate” iti | yathā — “ayam udayati mudrābhañjanaḥ padminīnām udayagirivanālī” ity ādau anukto 'ti sūrya udayatinā padmamudrābhañjanādinā ca lakṣyate | yady api kāvyapradīpe mukhyārthahatināmno doṣasya “ayam udayati mudrābhañjana” ity ādy udāharaṇam_ upanyastam, tathāpi niranurodhamukhyapadārthābhāve mukhyārthahatir doṣa ity avadheyam | iha tu buddhādipadollekhe kṛte dakṣiṇapathapathikasārthānām anupādeyatā syāt ; kṛṣnādipadoddeśe tu tat_kālakavalitamadoddhurāṇāṃ bauddhānām — ity ubhayasādhāraṇyena upādeyatārthaṃ mukhyārthānuddeśo na doṣāya | anye tv āhuḥ — “kvacid_ viśeṣaṇam_ api viśeṣyapratipattikaram | yathā — “nidhānagarbhām iva sāgarāmbarām” iti | ihāpi jñānadayāsindhvādiviśeṣaṇaṃ viśeṣyapratipattikaram_ ity adoṣaḥ |” śliṣṭarūpakākhyo 'yam alaṅkāraḥ || 1 || 
>Ṭīkāsarvasva
tatrādau bhagavataḥ sevāyāḥ paropadeśena prāripsitapratyūhapraśamanāya dharmamarjayann āha — yasyetyādi | he dhīrāḥ ! sa sevyatām ity anena dhairyaśālina eva sevituṃ śaknuvantīti tān sambodhayati | yasyānaghā guṇāḥ | anaghāḥ rāgādipāparahitāḥ | tathā cājayakośe — “aghaśabdo bhavet_ pāpe duḥkhavyasanayor api” guṇāḥ maitrīkṣamādayaḥ | jñānadayāsindhor iti | jñānaṃ samastavastuviṣayaṃ parijñānaṃ, dayā paraduḥkhaprahāṇecchā, tābhyāṃ sindhuḥ | ‘prakṛtyādibhya upasaṅkhyānam’ iti tṛtīyā | ‘tṛtīyā’ iti yogavibhāgāt_ samāsaḥ | sindhuśabdo vipulādhāratvād upacaritaḥ | sindhusāmyam evāha — agādhasya anyair anadhigatajñānadayāpāratvād aparicchedyagāmbhīryasya | akṣayaḥ parihitāpādaneṣu nāsti kṣayo vināśo yasyety akṣayaḥ | sindhupakṣe vyaktam evāgādhatvam akṣayatvaṃ ca | prayojanānupadarśane ca prekṣāvad apravṛtteḥ prayojanaṃ darśayati — śriyai cāmṛtāya ca | śriyai trivargasampattyai | tad uktaṃ vyāḍinā — “lakṣmīsarasvatī(dhātrī?)trivargasampadvibhūtiśobhāsu | upakaraṇaveṣaracanāvidhāsu ca śrīr iti prathitā ||” amṛtāya mokṣāya | cakārāv ubhayaprādhānyadyotanārtham | sindhur api surāsuraiḥ śriyai lakṣmyai amṛtāya pīyūṣāya ca sevitaḥ | atra cānukto 'pi śākyalakṣaṇo 'rtho jñānadayādibhiḥ spaṣṭaṃ pratīyata iti prasādanāmāyam arthaguṇaḥ | tad uktaṃ sarasvatīkaṇṭhābharaṇe — “yat tu prākaṭyam arthasya prasādaḥ so 'bhidhīyate | yathā — ayam udayati mudrābhañjanaḥ padminīnām udayagirivanālībālamandārapuṣpam | virahavidhur akokadvandvabandhur vibhindan_ kupitakapikapolakroḍatāmras tamāṃsi || atrānukto 'pi sūrya udayatīti padmamudrābhañjakatvādinā lakṣyate |” bauddhadarśanavidveṣiṇa iha pravṛttir na syād ity ato 'tra buddhapadopādānaṃ na kṛtaṃ kavinā | rūpakaṃ cāpy alaṅkāraḥ | tad uktaṃ daṇḍinā — “upamaiva tirobhūtabhedā rūpakam iṣyate | yathā bāhulatā pāṇipadmaṃ caraṇapallavaḥ ||” iti ||
>Vyākhāsudhā
prāripsitapratyūhāpanuttaye kṛtaṃ maṅgalaṃ śiṣyaśikṣārtham ādau nibabandha ― yasyeti || he anaghāḥ, bhavadbhiḥ sa dhīrāḥ sevyatām | na aghaṃ pāpaṃ yeṣāṃ te 'naghā niṣpāpāḥ | sukṛtina iti yāvat | sukṛtina eva taṃ sevituṃ prabhavantīti ta eva saṃbodhyante | ‘dharmeṇa pāpam apanudati’ iti śruteḥ | dhiyaṃ rāti dadāti | ‘rā dāne’ asmāt_ ‘kvip_ ca’ (3|2|76) iti kvip | dhīrāḥ jñānaprado guruḥ | anena ‘tadvijñānārthaṃ sa gurum evābhigacchet’ iti śrutyartha upadiṣṭaḥ | ‘prayojanam anuddiśya na mando 'pi pravartate’ iti gurusevāyāḥ phalam āha ― śriye cāmṛtāya ceti | cadvayam ubhayoḥ prādhānyadyotanāya | bhuktimuktiprāptir gurusevāto bhavati | ‘kriyārthopapadasya—’ iti caturthī | tādarthe vā | tad uktaṃ bhāgavate ― ‘yogarddhimāpurubhayīṃ yad uhaihayādyāḥ’ iti | nanu guroḥ śriyo 'bhāvāt tataḥ kathaṃ sā prār(pya)ta ity āśaṅkyāha ― yasyeti | asya guror ī lakṣmīr asti, guṇāś ca santi | tad uktaṃ bhāgavate ― ‘ṛte bhavatpādaparāyaṇān na māṃ vindanty ahaṃ tvaddhṛdayā yato 'jita’ iti | ‘satyaṃ śaucaṃ dayā kṣāntis tyāgaḥ saṃtoṣa ārjavam | śamo damas tapaḥ sāmyaṃ titikṣoparatiḥ śrutam || jñānaṃ viraktir aiśvaryaṃ śauryaṃ tejo balaṃ smṛtiḥ | svātantryaṃ kauśalaṃ kāntir dhairyaṃ mārdavam eva ca ||’ ity ādayo guṇāḥ | kīdṛśasyāsya ― jñānadayāsindhoḥ | jñāyato 'neneti jñānaṃ śāstram, dayā niṣkāraṇaparaduḥkhaprahāṇecchā, tayoḥ sindhor iva | śāstrasaṃpannasya, dayāpūrṇasya ca | anena ‘śrotriyaṃ brahmaniṣṭham’ iti viśeṣaṇayor madhye śrotriyatvam uktam | sa jñānavān api kim arthaṃ dāsyatīty ato dayāvattvam uktam | ‘dayālor asamarthasya duḥkhāyaiva dayālutā’ ity ato jñānavattvam uktam | kīdṛśasya ― agādhasya | na gādhas talasparśo yasya gambhīrasya | viṣayānākṛṣṭasyeti yāvat | yad vā agaṃ śailaṃ vṛkṣaṃ vā āpnoti | ‘anyebhyo 'pi dṛśyate’ iti āpnoteḥ iḥ | ṭilopaḥ | savarṇadīrghaḥ tam agāṃ dadhāti manasety agādhaḥ | tasya | parameśvarabhaktasyeti yāvat | kīdṛśo dhīrāḥ ― akṣayaḥ | aḥ vāsudevaḥ, tasmin_ kṣayo jñānaṃ nivāso vāsya so 'kṣayaḥ | anena brahmaniṣṭhatārūpaṃ dvitīyaṃ viśeṣaṇam uktam | yad vā na kṣayo hiṃsā yasya | ‘kṣīṣ_ hiṃsāyām’ ‘erac’ | pūrvatra tu ‘kṣi nivāsagatyoḥ’ parapīḍāpahārakaḥ | ‘yasmān nodvijate lokaḥ’ iti gītā | athavā sa dhīrāḥ mayā sevyatām | sa kaḥ | yasya guṇā anaghāḥ | na aghaṃ yebhyas te 'naghāḥ | pāpanivartakā iti yāvat | ‘yaśaḥ kalimalāpaham’ iti bhāgavatāt | śeṣaṃ samānam | ‘āśiṣi liṅ_loṭau’ iti karmaṇi loṭ | itthaṃ hi gurusevāparān_ prati kartavyatvenopadiśyate svayaṃ vā prārthyate | gurusevāmāhātmyaṃ ca brahmavaivartādau prasiddham | bhāgavate 'pi ― ‘yathā'haṃ jñānado guruḥ’ iti, ‘tuṣyeyaṃ sarvabhūtātmā guruśuśrūṣayā yathā’ iti ca | evaṃ ‘lakṣmīvān, kalyāṇa(nirmala)guṇaḥ, śāstrasaṃpanno, dayāpūrṇo, viṣayānākṛṣṭo, viṣṇubhakto, viṣṇusākṣātkāravān, jñānado, guruḥ saṃpatprāptyarthaṃ mokṣaprāptyarthaṃ ca niṣpāpair adhikāribhiḥ, mayā vā sevyatām’ iti parebhyo hitam upadiśan, svahitam āśaṃsamāno vā granthakṛdāśīrvādalakṣaṇam (iti) lakṣmīsmaraṇalakṣaṇaṃ ca maṅgalam ācacāra | yat tu mukuṭaḥ ― ‘sveṣṭadevatāsaṃkīrtanād viśiṣṭādṛṣṭam utpipādayiṣu’ ity avocat | tan na | devatāvācakapadasyātrādarśanāt, āśirloṭo darśanāc ca | svāmī tu ― ‘jinam anusmṛtya’ iti smaraṇalakṣaṇaṃ maṅgalam āha | tan na | jinavācakapadasyātrādarśanāt, sāmānyaśabdānāṃ jinalakṣaṇaviśeṣaparatvena vyākhyānasya vaidikānām anucitatvāt, amarakartur jainatve pramāṇābhāvāc ca | prāñcas tu ― ‘he dhīrāḥ, sa bhagavān_ sevyatām ārādhyatām | dhairyaśālina eva sevitum śaknuvantīti tān eva saṃbodhayati | prakṛtatvād yuṣmābhir hitecchubhiḥ | sa kaḥ ― yasya guṇā maitrīmaryādādayo 'ṇimādayo vā anaghā niṣpāpāḥ | rāgādyasaṃvalitā iti yāvat | yad vā, hṛdyāḥ | tathā ca dharaṇiḥ ― ‘anagho 'pāpahṛdyayoḥ’ iti | kiṃbhūtasya ― jñānadayāsindhoḥ | jñānaṃ samastavi(ṣayā)vabodhaḥ | dṛṣṭaṃ svārtham anapekṣya paraduḥkhaprahāṇecchā dayā | tayor ambutulyayoḥ sindhor iva sindhor vipulādhārasya, agādhasya anavacchinnamahimnaḥ | anyair anadhigatajñānapāratvād aparicche(dyaṃ gāmbhīryaṃ ya)sya vā | sa kiṃbhūtaḥ ― parahitāpādaneṣu nāsti kṣayo virāmo yasya, maraṇādirāhityād vā | phalādhīnaiva prekṣāvatāṃ pravṛttir ata āha ― śriye cety ādi | śrir atra trivargasaṃpattiḥ, tāṃ prāptum, amṛtāya mokṣāya ca | yad vā ― sa sindhuḥ sevyatām | sa kaḥ ― yasya agādhasyātalasparśasya, akṣayasya sadā paripūrṇasya, asya viṣṇoḥ kṣayasya nivāsasya vā guṇāḥ, anaghā ratnādimattvān nairmalyādayaḥ, śriye lakṣmyai, amṛtāya ca pīyūṣāya ca’ ity āhuḥ | atra samudrapakṣas tu na samyag iva | jñānety asyānanvayāt | ‘akṣayaḥ’ ity asya prathamāntasya ṣaṣṭhyantatvena vyākhyānasyānucitatvāt | ‘abhīṣṭadevatānamaskārādyupanītam adṛṣṭaṃ hi ―’ ity ādi svagranthavirodhāc ca | āśīrnamaskriyāvastunirdeśeṣv anantarbhāvāt | ‘jñānadayayoḥ syandate pravartate devatārūpatvāt’ iti vā, ‘jñānadaye syandete pravartete devatārūpe 'smin‘ iti vā samādheyam || ṣaṣṭhyartho 'py ārthikārthatvena samādhātuṃ śakyaḥ | ‘syandateḥ saṃprasāraṇaṃ dhaś ca’ ity uḥ || yat tu mukuṭaḥ ― tābhyāṃ sindhur iveti prakṛtyāditvāt tṛtīyā | ‘tṛtīyā’ iti yogavibhāgāt_ samāsaḥ’ iti sarvadharādayaḥ | iti || tad api na samyak | arthāsaṃgateḥ || prātipadikārthe hi sā, tasya na bhedenābhedena vātrānvayaḥ saṃbhavati || abhede hi tṛtīyā vyarthā | prathamāyā evaucityāt || 1 ||
>Amaradīpikā
